3. TCL & DCL COMMANDS

 
a) TCL COMMANDS 


 1. Commit 
 
mysql> set autocommit=0;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)

mysql> INSERT INTO student  VALUES(6,'Neiira',45);
Query OK, 1 row affected (0.00 sec)

mysql> select*from student;
+------------+--------+------+
| rollnumber | name   | age  |
+------------+--------+------+
|          6 | Neiira |   45 |
+------------+--------+------+
1 row in set (0.00 sec)
 
 2. Rollback 
 
mysql> commit;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)

mysql> set autocommit=0;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)

mysql> INSERT INTO student  VALUES(7,'Neiira',46);
Query OK, 1 row affected (0.00 sec)

mysql> select*from student;
+------------+--------+------+
| rollnumber | name   | age  |
+------------+--------+------+
|          7 | Neiira |   46 |
+------------+--------+------+
1 row in set (0.00 sec)

mysql> rollback;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.05 sec)

mysql> select*from student;
Empty set (0.00 sec)
 
